descript.abstract: The Massachusetts Senate Legislative Districts (2002) datalayer reflects the state Senate district boundaries as defined by Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 57: Section 3. These 40 districts are those used in the Fall 2002 elections. Names of elected officials are up-to-date as of January 2009. The names of the statewide datalayers are SENATE02_POLY (polygons) and SENATE02_ARC (arcs). This replaces the older SENATE93 layer.

procstep.procdesc:
Staff at the Massachusetts Senate developed this layer with its contracor, Caliper Corp. (Newton, MA) using Maptitude for Redistricting software. MassGIS appended the 1:100,000 coastline and state outline and added the senators' name and party attributes. Final election results were obtained from a "Return of Votes" report (in PDF format) from the Secretary of State.
Massgis maintains the layer and will make updates as needed. In March 2003 the boundary between Sen. Fargo's district and that of Sen. Jacques was adjusted.
In April, 2004, the polygon attributes were changed to reflect Sen. Scott Brown replacing Sen. Cheryl Jacques in the Norfolk, Bristol, and Middlesex district.
In January, 2005, attribute updates were made to reflect changes based on the November, 2004 elections. In April, 2005, the attributes for the Second Middlesex district were edited following the death of Sen. Shannon. In October, 2005, the attributes were edited, as Patricia Jehlen filled Sen. Shannon's open seat.
In January, 2007, attribute updates were made to reflect changes based on the November, 2006, elections. In October, 2007, attributes were edited for three senatorial changes. In March 2008 attributes were edited after special elections to fill two vacant seats.
